IN	2 tablespoons white wine vinegar
IN	2 tablespoons whole grain dijon mustard
IN	2 tablespoons minced shallot
IN	1 garlic clove, minced
IN	1/4 cup extra-virgin olive oil
IN	6 cups frisée, torn into bite-size pieces
IN	2 cups torn radicchio leaves
IN	2 large heads of Belgian endive, cut crosswise into 1/2-inch strips
IN	2 tablespoons chopped fresh chives
IN	2 tablespoons coarsely chopped fresh cilantro
IN	2 tablespoons fresh tarragon leaves
PR	Whisk vinegar, mustard, shallot, and garlic in small bowl. Gradually whisk in oil. Season dressing with salt and pepper.
PR	Toss frisée and all remaining ingredients in large bowl. Add dressing; toss to coat. Season with salt and pepper.
